text:
Aquinas Football Prepares for State's Top-Ranked Side 
Updated: Tuesday, October 13 2015, 11:22 PM EDT 
Do not ask Aquinas to talk about the last time the Lil' Irish played Canisius. Last season, the Griffins not only beat AQ, but knocked the section's top player, Jake Zembiec, out for the season. But, the Irish are quick to say this isn't about redemption. Likewise, Aquinas will be the best team on the Griffins schedule. Per usual, both squads are ranked in the state's top-3 - adding another high-profile chapter in what's become the state's hottest rivalry. 13WHAM-TV's Jon Doss has the story.
